The paper deals with a distributed consensus algorithm, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of electric networks and random walks suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). Information theory (cs.IT) is also relevant to the analysis of distributed algorithms. Neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY) may also be relevant due to the use of Markov chains and couplings.
